transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for calling. This is John. How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Hey John, this is Joe. I just have a question about my order that came.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Do you need my phone number or what?

Speaker 1: Your last name and zip code?

Speaker 2: Abolese. A-V-O-L-E-S-E-1-1-7-4-7.

Speaker 1: I got you pulled up here, Joe. What can I help you with?

Speaker 2: Okay. So, um, I just wanted to make sure the reason I switched to your company is that you have the new pills that, you know, what do they call them?

Speaker 1: The A-G-V.

Speaker 2: Right. Right. And that's what you sent me.

Speaker 1: That's what I see on my side here that you got 25 to 100 milligram A-G-V pills. Do the pills themselves have 100 stamped on the pill?

Speaker 2: Yes, they do.

Speaker 1: Okay. And that is the A-G-V pill. I know some of our marketing shows different, like a slightly different looking pill, but it should be a white diamond that says 100. So, that's, you got the right one, sir.

Speaker 2: Okay. No, the reason I was confused is because the advertiser in that, it starts to be effective in 11 minutes, but I don't know what this one says, take one hour.

Speaker 1: Oh, oh, yes. Yeah, I can answer that question too. So, the reason it says that is because we cannot promise every single person is going to react the same way.

Speaker 1: So, to avoid anybody being in an embarrassing situation the first couple of times they take it, we suggest do the hour. But once you've tried it a time or two, you'll get a better sense of how quickly it works for you.

Speaker 2: Okay. So, it's definitely faster acting than the old Viagra?

Speaker 1: Yes, sir. Most commonly I hear people tell me about 15 to 20 minutes is when it starts to kick in.

Speaker 2: Okay, great. All right. Well, I appreciate your help.

Speaker 1: You're welcome, Joe. I hope you have a good one.

Speaker 2: Thanks for your help. Bye-bye.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.
